# Phase 5: Audit Log System

This plan outlines the approach to tracking critical system actions across all modules for full traceability, ensuring all operations log the `storeId`, `userId`, `action`, and state changes.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The audit log collection (`audit_logs`) will quickly grow in size. While Firestore is highly scalable, you may eventually want to set up an automated script (like a Firebase Cloud Function) to archive logs older than 90 days. For now, we will focus solely on the tracking implementation.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Audit Hook
#### [NEW] [useAudit.js](file:///c:/Users/praga/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/jewellery-website/src/hooks/useAudit.js)
- Build a generic `logAudit(action, module, entityId, oldValue, newValue)` function.
- Automatically inject `userId` and `storeId` using the active session from `AppContext`.

